news.title: First phase of Mumbai's metro line three to be commissioned soon
news.para: Addressing a press conference, Ashwini Bhide, managing director for Mumbai Metro Rail Corporation (MMRC), said the Metro Line 3 is poised to be commissioned very soon, subject to clearance by the Commissioner of Metro Railway Safety (CMRS).

news.title: Britain's NewRiver REIT to buy Capital & Regional in $196 million deal
news.para: The deal comes at a time of stabilising property values in the British commercial property sector and increased deal-making activity on the back of improved rental growth prospects.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh's industrial authorities to adopt standard building bylaws
news.para: Tasked with the responsibility of allocating land parcels to investors, the department of infrastructure and industrial development is carrying out works through eight different industrial development authorities involved with the process of aggregating and developing large land tracts across the state.

news.title: China announces significant support to boost property market
news.para: The People’s Bank of China will cut outstanding mortgage rates for individual borrowers by an average of 0.5 percentage point, Governor Pan Gongsheng said at a press conference on Tuesday. The minimum down-payment ratio on second home purchases will be lowered to 15% from 25%.

news.title: Register seven crore workers associated with real estate with ESIC, PF: Commerce minister
news.para: "I urge you to kindly think about this in very serious terms... can we ensure a guaranteed ESIC and provident fund registration of all these 70 million workmen and women (working in this sector)," Goyal told real estate players.

news.title: Arkade Developers shares surge over 37% in market debut on September 24
news.para: At the NSE, shares of the firm listed at Rs 175, reflecting a jump of 36.71 per cent. The company's market valuation stood at Rs 3,232.40 crore. The initial share sale of Arkade Developers got subscribed 106.40 times on the last day of the offer on Thursday.

news.title: Croatia to shift tax burden to property to tackle housing problem
news.para: There are 600,000 properties either empty or only available for short-term rent in the country of 3.85 million people, making it hard for younger people to find long-term apartment lets, especially in coastal Adriatic tourist towns.

news.title: DPR for Ujjain's proposed IT Park ready, development in two phases
news.para: "We have procured the transfer of 2.16 hectare of land from the administration for constructing Ujjain's pioneering IT Park, and the DRP has also been submitted. The development will transpire in two stages, with the initial phase anticipated to incur a cost of approximately Rs 67 crore," said Rajesh Rathod, the executive director of MPIDC, Ujjain.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body forms special squads to keep check on illegal C&D disposal
news.para: Now, C&D sanitation squads will be formed for all seven zones of the city to conduct checks and penalise individuals or institutions found dumping C&D waste on roads, footpaths or public places. The fines range from Rs 25,000 to Rs 1 lakh.

news.title: Pune: Residents protest against impending demolition drive in blue floodline zone
news.para: The residents claim the civic body should build a retaining wall along the river instead of demolishing their houses that have been there for over 30-40 years, as many people have spent their life earnings to construct a house or purchase a flat in the zone.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: All plots at Sinhasa IT Park to allocated by year-end
news.para: Of the total 53 plots in Sinhasa IT Park, MPSEDC has allotted 33 plots to IT/ITES players, with a proposed investment exceeding Rs 100 crore, according to officials.

news.title: Fingerprint scanners upgraded for safe land registration in Tamil Nadu
news.para: Across the state every day, on average, 15,000 documents are registered and 50,000 fingerprints are authenticated in the 582 sub-registrar offices under the state registration department. The department has been using fingerprint scanners along with Aadhaar authentication and EKYC while registering documents. "If a person purchases a property, his/her fingerprint is registered.

news.title: Nashik civic body to make hand over of C&D waste mandatory for all builders
news.para: A civic official, while talking to TOI, said once the plant becomes operational, the developers will have to inform the municipal administration while seeking building permission about the C&D waste that would be generated at their construction sites.

news.title: Residents call for action against commercial complex in Hyderabad's Nandagiri Hills
news.para: Residents of Nandagiri Hills in Jubilee Hills are opposing a multi-storey commercial complex being constructed on 4.7 acres, alleging it violates building norms. They claim the builder merged two plots to secure GHMC permissions without proper inspections, raising legal and environmental concerns.

news.title: Promoters should not offer possession on terms to restrict legal rights of allottees: UP-RERA
news.para: The authority is preparing to take cognizance of the complaints received against such promoters to protect the rights and interests of the allottees and suitable action will also be taken against the promoters, if found guilty.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM opens two Neo Tidel parks in Thanjavur and Salem
news.para: These facilities, each having a built-up area of 55,000 sq ft and built as G+3 structures are part of the govt's effort to take information technology jobs to tier-II and tier-III cities in the state.

news.title: ITAT sends case on tax deduction for adjoining flats back for reverification
news.para: During 2020-21, the taxpayer, P Shah, had claimed a tax deduction of Rs 9.5 crore under Section 54-F of the Income-Tax (I-T) Act, following her investment in two adjoining flats in Navi Mumbai.

news.title: ED attaches assets of Sai Construction and Builders' partner under PMLA
news.para: ED initiated an investigation based on an FIR registered by CBI, Ghaziabad, (UP) under various sections of IPC, 1860, and the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988, against M/s Sai Construction and Builders, Ghaziabad, and its partners and others for alleged loan fraud.

news.title: Haryana: HSVP blacklists 18 architects for issuing illegal occupancy certificates
news.para: The chief town planner of the HSVP has now written to the senior officials of the information technology department ordering removal of the blacklisted architects' IDs from the online building plan approval system.

news.title: Gujarat RERA orders builders to open project-linked bank accounts within state
news.para: The directive was issued after the authority discovered that numerous developers, particularly those in South Gujarat, maintained project-linked bank accounts in branches located in Maharashtra, which could hinder the effective implementation of GujRERA orders.
